    "chemicalDescription": [
      "s-Goat Nonapeptide-1 is a single chain peptide consisting of asparagine, glycine, isoleucine, phenylalanine, proline and tyrosine. It is synthetically produced based on a sequence from Beta-Casein found in the goat. The parent protein contains a maximum of 222 amino acids which may contain disulfide bonds and/or glycosylation, and consists of the proper sequence from the 20 standard amino acids."
